         <abstract>
            <p>Disagreement persists in the literature regarding the appropriate method for the evaluation of the lease versus purchase alternatives. Most of the controversy stems from the interaction that exists in this case between investment and financial decisions. This paper provides an analytical framework which resolves this controversy by directly neutralizing the impact of the lease contract on the firm's financial structure and debt capacity.</p>
